Revision history for arcanum

0.01  2026-03-16
    - Initial release implementing the full MVP feature set (plan steps 1-20).

    Scan phase:
      - FileClassifier: git-status-aware file walker with age scoring and
        package-manager origin detection (Path::Tiny iterator)
      - ArchiveHandler: recursive archive traversal for .tar, .tar.gz,
        .tar.bz2, .tar.xz, .zip, .gz with disk-space guard and nesting limit

    Format parsers (lib/App/Arcanum/Format/):
      - PlainText: line-by-line plain text
      - CSV: Text::CSV_XS with header-column PII hinting
      - JSON: Cpanel::JSON::XS recursive key walk
      - YAML: YAML::XS recursive walk
      - LDIF: Net::LDAP::LDIF attribute scan
      - MongoDB: JSON Lines / mongoexport format
      - Spreadsheet: XLS (Spreadsheet::ParseExcel) and XLSX (ParseXLSX)
      - ICS: Data::ICal attendee/organiser/summary/description
      - Mbox: Mail::Box::Manager + Email::MIME headers and body parts
      - Sieve: custom parser for email addresses in string literals

    Detectors (lib/App/Arcanum/Detector/):
      - Email address (RFC 5321 + obfuscated variants)
      - Phone number (E.164, NANP, common international)
      - US SSN (format + range validation)
      - Credit/debit card (Luhn + BIN prefix)
      - Person name (given + family name lists)
      - Physical address (street number + road type heuristic)
      - Date of birth (multi-format with context requirement)
      - Passport number (ICAO 9303 Machine Readable Zone)
      - UK National Insurance Number
      - Canadian SIN
      - Australian Tax File Number
      - IBAN (ISO 13616 checksum)
      - VIN (ISO 3779)
      - Medical record ID
      - National ID (generic)
      - IP address (v4 and v6)
      - MAC address
      - Secrets / API keys / private keys
      - CLI-embedded credentials (--password=, --token=, env vars, PEM headers)
      - Full email content (headers + quoted-printable body)
      - Calendar event PII
      - Plugin-based detector (JSON Lines IPC via IPC::Open2)

    Special file handling (lib/App/Arcanum/SpecialFiles.pm):
      - Shell history files (.bash_history, .zsh_history, etc.)
      - Editor artefacts (.swp, .swo, Vim undo files, Emacs #backup#)
      - Credential files (id_rsa, .netrc, .pgpass, etc.)
      - Image EXIF metadata (Image::ExifTool; GPS coordinates → high severity)

    Tombstoning (lib/App/Arcanum/Tombstone.pm):
      - SHA-256 index built from .arcanum-tombstones JSON Lines files
      - Per-file hash check during scan; critical finding on match
      - Tombstone entry written by Deleter after each deletion

    Remediation (lib/App/Arcanum/Remediation/):
      - Redactor: in-place value replacement for CSV, JSON, YAML, plain text
      - Quarantine: move file to .arcanum-quarantine/ with JSON metadata
      - Deleter: unlink (or shred) + tombstone write; audit log entry
      - GitRewriter: git filter-repo integration for history rewriting
      - Encryptor: GPG-encrypt file and securely delete plaintext original

    Reports (lib/App/Arcanum/Report/):
      - Text: human-readable coloured STDOUT report
      - JSON: machine-readable with schema_version, per-framework summaries,
        critical value truncation (41***11)
      - HTML: self-contained single-file report with inline CSS, collapsible
        file blocks, copy-to-clipboard git rewrite commands
      - ComplianceMap: GDPR/PCI-DSS/HIPAA/CCPA framework tagging, RoPA skeleton,
        retention gap analysis, data subject request lookup

    Notifications (lib/App/Arcanum/Notification/):
      - Email (Net::SMTP)
      - Webhook (HTTP::Tiny — Slack, Teams, generic)
      - GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket PR comment APIs
      - Dispatcher: routes to all configured back-ends

    Configuration (lib/App/Arcanum/Config.pm):
      - JSONC relaxed parsing (Cpanel::JSON::XS)
      - Search order: --config flag, CWD, ~/.config, /etc, built-in defaults
      - Profile preset overlay (gdpr, pci_dss, hipaa, server, laptop)
      - Level enforcement: profiles can only raise scanning levels

    CLI (bin/arcanum):
      - Subcommands: scan, full, config --check, config --dump, help
      - --execute flag required for any file modification
      - --profile, --level, --dry-run, --verbose, --quiet, --no-color

    Test suite: 1049 tests across 27 test files (prove -l t/ → PASS)
